question.title: Weird art runtime error Eclipse - Android

node.contents: This only happens when you try to upload your app over adb? I wouldn't worry about it. It looks like the runtime is dieing due to a SIGABRT, which adb probably issues when it's going to replace an apk or something.

astNode.text: This only happens when you try to upload your app over adb? I wouldn't worry about it. It looks like the runtime is dieing due to a SIGABRT, which adb probably issues when it's going to replace an apk or something.

node.contents: I have a very weird issue. Sometimes, randomly and without any noticeable pattern, I encounter this ART runtime error that causes my app to stop. Out of all of the random and few times this has occurred, it is always happening when I am downloading the program to my testing device. If I restart the download, it is fine and the error does not appear. This is the log of my error:
